Chee-Yong Chan is an Associate Professor in the 
<A HREF="http://www.comp.nus.edu.sg/cs/">Computer Science Department</A>
at the 
<A HREF="http://www.nus.edu.sg">National University of Singapore</A>.
He received his B.Sc. (Hons) and M.Sc. degrees in Computer Science
from the National University of Singapore,
and his Ph.D. degree in Computer Science
from the 
<A HREF="http://www.cs.wisc.edu">University of Wisconsin-Madison</A>.
He was a Member of Technical Staff at 
<A HREF="http://www.bell-labs.com">Bell Labs</A>,
<A HREF="http://www.lucent.com">Lucent Technologies</A>
prior to his return to <A HREF="http://www.visitsingapore.com">Singapore</A>.
His current research interests include data analytics, database usability, query processing and optimization.


